{"title":"Bind Souls","url":"http://crawl.chaosforge.org/Bind_Souls","type":"markdown","data":"***Version [0.30](/0.30 \"0.30\")**: This article **may not be** up to date for the [latest stable release](/0.32 \"0.32\") of Crawl.*\n\n*This page refers to the monster spell. For the god-granted ability, see [Yredelemnul](/Yredelemnul \"Yredelemnul\").*\n\n|   |                                                                                                                  |\n| - | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n|   | Bestows an enchantment on other nearby living creatures that causes them to rise as simulacra after being slain. |\n\n**Bind Souls** is a monsters-only spell that enchants all living creatures in the caster's LOS for some time. When an enchanted creature is slain, a [simulacrum](/Simulacrum_\\(monster\\) \"Simulacrum (monster)\") matching them will be created in the vicinity. This spell also prevents your own undead-creating [Necromancy](/Necromancy \"Necromancy\") (except [Death Channel](/Death_Channel \"Death Channel\")) from working.\n\nThe following enemies cast Bind Souls:\n\n- L [![Josephina.png](/images/1/1d/Josephina.png)](/File:Josephina.png) **[Josephina](/Josephina \"Josephina\")**\n- p [![Necromancer.png](/images/5/5d/Necromancer.png)](/File:Necromancer.png) **[Necromancer (monster)](/Necromancer_\\(monster\\) \"Necromancer (monster)\")**\n\nAdditionally, the following monsters cast Bind Souls automatically when slain:\n\n- B [![Pharaoh ant.png](/images/a/a2/Pharaoh_ant.png)](/File:Pharaoh_ant.png) **[Pharaoh ant](/Pharaoh_ant \"Pharaoh ant\")**\n\nFollowers of [Gozag](/Gozag \"Gozag\") effectively neuter this spell; corpses turn into gold before they can turn into simulacrum.\n\n## History\n\n- Prior to [0.30](/0.30 \"0.30\"), [Gozag](/Gozag \"Gozag\") didn't block hostile soul binding.\n- Prior to [0.27](/0.27 \"0.27\"), a simulacrum would only appear if an enchanted monster would drop a [corpse](/Corpse \"Corpse\"). That is, the spell only had a 50% chance to create a simulacrum on death.\n- Bind Souls was introduced in [0.19](/0.19 \"0.19\").\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Bind Souls - CrawlWiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Bind_Souls\",\"wgTitle\":\"Bind Souls\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":76039,\"wgRevisionId\":76039,\"wgArticleId\":10262,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":null,\"wgUserGroups\":[\"*\"],\"wgCategories\":[\"0.30 articles\",\"Monster spells\"],\"wgBreakFrames\":false,\"wgPageContentLanguage\":\"en\",\"wgPageContentModel\":\"wikitext\",\"wgSeparatorTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDigitTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDefaultDateFormat\":\"dmy\",\"wgMonthNames\":[\"\",\"January\",\"February\",\"March\",\"April\",\"May\",\"June\",\"July\",\"August\",\"September\",\"October\",\"November\",\"December\"],\"wgMonthNamesShort\":[\"\",\"Jan\",\"Feb\",\"Mar\",\"Apr\",\"May\",\"Jun\",\"Jul\",\"Aug\",\"Sep\",\"Oct\",\"Nov\",\"Dec\"],\"wgRelevantPageName\":\"Bind_Souls\",\"wgRelevantArticleId\":10262,\"wgRequestId\":\"f4ad2a5469b810fc31d6482e\",\"wgIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRelevantPageIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRestrictionEdit\":[],\"wgRestrictionMove\":[]});mw.loader.state({\"site.styles\":\"ready\",\"noscript\":\"ready\",\"user.styles\":\"ready\",\"user\":\"ready\",\"user.options\":\"loading\",\"user.tokens\":\"loading\",\"ext.smw.style\":\"ready\",\"ext.smw.tooltip.styles\":\"ready\",\"mediawiki.legacy.shared\":\"ready\",\"mediawiki.legacy.commonPrint\":\"ready\",\"mediawiki